==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tetradrachma
<hw>Tet`ra*drach"ma</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. <ets>tetradrachma</ets>,
fr. Gr. <grk>tetra`drachmon</grk>; <grk>te`tra-</grk> (see
<er>Tetra-</er>) + <grk>drachmh`</grk> drachm, drachma.]</ety> <def>A
silver coin among the ancient Greeks, of the value of four
drachms.</def> <note>The Attic <ex>tetradrachm</ex> was equal to 3s. 3d.
sterling, or about 76 cents.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

